    label "3"
    text " coral reef ecology is an incredibly rich field because reefs are among the most biodiverse ecosystems on the planet"
  ]
  node [
    id 4
    label "4"
    text " Even though they occupy less than 1% of the ocean floor, they support roughly 25% of marine life, from tiny invertebrates to large predators"
  ]
  node [
    id 5
    label "5"
    text " Corals are animals, not plants, and they live in a symbiotic relationship with zooxanthellae&#8212;photosynthetic algae that live inside their tissues"
  ]
  node [
    id 6
    label "6"
    text " This relationship provides corals with nutrients and is responsible for their vibrant colors"
  ]
  node [
    id 7
    label "7"
    text " But it&#8217;s also why they&#8217;re so sensitive to temperature change"
  ]
  node [
    id 8
    label "8"
    text " When ocean temperatures rise&#8212;even by just 1 or 2 degrees Celsius&#8212;corals expel their algae, leading to a process called bleaching"
  ]
  node [
    id 9
    label "9"
    text " If the stress continues, they can die, leading to reef collapse"
  ]
  node [
    id 10
    label "10"
    text " Climate change and ocean acidification are major threats to reefs globally, and mass bleaching events have increased in frequency and severity"
  ]
  node [
    id 11
    label "11"
    text " We also study local stressors like overfishing, coastal development, and nutrient runoff"
  ]
  node [
    id 12
    label "12"
    text " These factors weaken reef systems and reduce their resilience"
  ]
  node [
    id 13
    label "13"
    text " Healthy reefs depend on a balance between coral growth, herbivore activity (like grazing fish), and the physical structure of the reef itself"
  ]
  node [
    id 14
    label "14"
    text " Restoration efforts are underway in many parts of the world"
  ]
  node [
    id 15
    label "15"
    text " Some involve coral gardening&#8212;growing fragments in nurseries and transplanting them"
  ]
  node [
    id 16
    label "16"
    text " Others look at selective breeding for heat-resistant corals"
  ]
  node [
    id 17
    label "17"
    text " But restoration is not a silver bullet"
  ]
  node [
    id 18
    label "18"
    text " Without addressing climate change, we&#8217;re just delaying the inevitable"
  ]
  node [
    id 19
    label "19"
    text " Still, reefs are incredibly dynamic"
  ]
  node [
    id 20
    label "20"
    text " If we give them the right conditions&#8212;stable temperatures, clean water, biodiversity&#8212;they can regenerate"
  ]
  node [
    id 21
    label "21"
    text " Protecting them is not just about saving fish; it&#8217;s about preserving coastline protection, food systems, and cultural heritage"
